* a la jquery
* concisify selection of DOM elements 
* eg.some D3 selector functions:

d3.select( IDENTIFIER );
	returns first element matching

so why d3?
	after selecting an element, yu can set various attributes: style, 
	txt. listeners, etc,.
d3.select("body").


d3.selectAll("p")
	.style("font-size",
	function(){
		return Math.floor(Math.random() * 15)
		 + "px"
		 }
		);
